# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  deepcopilot — Configuration                                  ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the key(s) for the provider(s)
# you want to use:   cp .env.example .env
#
# This proxy speaks the OpenAI Chat Completions API to GitHub Copilot
# and routes each request to a backend based on the requested model.

# ── Default backend ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by the CLI when you run without -b, and by the "auto" model.
# Options: nvidia, deepseek, kimi
API_PROVIDER=nvidia

# ── Port ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Defaults to Ollama's port (11434) so deepcopilot is a drop-in
# replacement: Copilot's built-in "Ollama" provider points at
# http://localhost:11434 out of the box, so no extra setup is needed.
# Change this only if you actually run real Ollama on 11434.
DEEPCOPILOT_PORT=11434

# ── Nvidia NIM  (OpenAI-compatible — passthrough) ────────────
# Get your key: https://build.nvidia.com
# Only the key is required — a curated list of Nvidia models is built in
# and shown in Copilot's picker automatically. To override the list, set
# NVIDIA_MODELS to a comma-separated list of model ids (browse them at
# https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1/models). Ids with '/' appear in the
# picker with '/' replaced by '__'. Append ":<tokens>" to set a model's
# context window, e.g. stepfun-ai/step-3.7-flash:262144
NVIDIA_API_KEY=nvapi-your-nvidia-key
# NVIDIA_MODELS=stepfun-ai/step-3.7-flash:262144, moonshotai/kimi-k2.6

# ── DeepSeek  (OpenAI-compatible — passthrough) ──────────────
# Get your key: https://platform.deepseek.com  (built-in: v4-pro, v4-flash)
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-your-deepseek-key
# DEEPSEEK_MODELS=deepseek-v4-pro, deepseek-v4-flash

# ── Kimi for coding  (Anthropic-native — translated) ─────────
# Get your key: https://www.kimi.com/code/console
# NOTE: this is Kimi *for coding* (api.kimi.com/coding), not the
# OpenAI-compatible Moonshot platform.
KIMI_API_KEY=sk-your-kimi-key
# KIMI_MODELS=kimi-for-coding

# ── DeepSeek OAuth Web  (chat.deepseek.com browser session — TEXT ONLY) ─
# Drives the web chat (not the paid API). Auth is your browser session, not
# an API key. NO tool calling — chat/agent text only. deepseek-v4-pro with
# thinking ON, 1M context. Fragile: the token + WAF cookie expire (minutes
# to hours) and replaying them may violate DeepSeek's ToS — personal use.
#   TOKEN:  chat.deepseek.com → F12 → Application → Local Storage →
#           key "userToken" → copy its "value".
#   COOKIE: F12 → Network → any api/v0 request → Request Headers → copy the
#           full "cookie:" value (must include ds_session_id + aws-waf-token).
# DEEPSEEK_OAUTH_WEB_TOKEN=<your userToken value>
# DEEPSEEK_OAUTH_WEB_MODEL=deepseek-v4-pro-1m   # picker label only (web picks the model); kept distinct from Nvidia's deepseek-ai/deepseek-v4-pro (~160k)
# DEEPSEEK_OAUTH_WEB_COOKIE=aws-waf-token=...; ds_session_id=...

# ── Debug (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to 1 to log routing + upstream status to stderr.
# DEEPCOPILOT_DEBUG=1
